MESSAGE.value: Adhering as much as I can to the MVC design pattern (new to me) I was able to work on the following: - Model o Player model - Views: o Player names view o Spin wheel view o Ask question view o Start new round view (screenshot not shown) o Game is over view (screenshot not shown) o Give answer view - Controllers: o Player names controller o Spin wheel controller o Ask question controller o Give answer controller

- Added spin counter display on all relevant screens. - Work on “Jeopardy ask question” screen: o Added countdown timer o Implemented “spin” button action o Implemented “show answer” button action - Questions AND answers are now automatically populated on the screens via the JSON file data. - Implemented “dummy” actions when the yes/no radio buttons are pressed to self-report answer correctness. o The “dummy” action is a text message in the console. - Controllers added: o StartNewRoundController o GameIsOverController - Work on “Round is Over” screen: o Screen is displayed when spinCounter = 0 for a given round o Implemented “start new round” button action - Work on “Game is Over” screen: o Screen is displayed upon finishing the 2 rounds of the game NOTE: No actions have been implemented on the elements of this screen, though.
